user.biography: Welcome to the official Visit California Instagram feed. Use #VisitCalifornia for a chance to be featured.

node.text:
Teresa Baker is building a more inclusive future for the outdoor industry. In this story from @theoutbound, follow her journey as she and a group of diverse outdoor leaders become some of the first members of the public to explore #HaroldRichardsonRedwoodsReserve. It's a massive old-growth redwood grove recently protected by @savetheredwoods in @SonomaCounty.
.
#VisitCalifornia #EveryoneOutside

node.text:
The largest municipal park in the country, #GriffithPark in @discoverla has 53 miles of trails to hike and is made up of 4,300 acres of jaw-dropping views. Here are the five things you have to do when you're there! ⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #discoverLA

node.title: 5 Amazing Things to Do at Griffith Park

⁣
What else do you love to do at #ChannelIslandsNationalPark?⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

node.text:
As if we needed another excuse to stop by @VisitLodi for a casual wine tasting trip... ⁣
⁣
A well-known producer of the hearty Zinfandel wine varietal, Lodi is also a leader in the sustainability space. In 2005, local winegrowers pioneered the Lodi Rules, California’s first third-party certified sustainable viticulture program. Here are some of the wineries keeping green practices at heart: ⁣
🍷 @bergholdvineyard⁣
🍷 @jessiesgrovewinery⁣
🍷 @michaeldavidwinery
🍷 @st.amant_wine⁣
⁣
Have you checked out #LodiWineCountry yet? Which winery was your first stop? ⁣
⁣
📷: David H. Collier, @ashannon95
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #VisitLodi

node.text:
Welcome to Denmark (in California!) 🇩🇰 Here are some things you may not know about @SolvangUSA, our little Danish hamlet in @VisitSYV. ⁣
⁣
🇩🇰 #Solvang is Danish for "sunny field" ⁣
🇩🇰 The town was founded in 1911 by Danish Americans from the Midwest. ⁣
🇩🇰 There are four wooden windmills in four blocks. ⁣
🇩🇰 Find a replica of Copenhagen's famous "Little Mermaid" sculpture on the corner of Mission Drive and Lisal Road. ⁣
⁣
Oh, we almost forgot – pastries. You can't skip a Danish and coffee from Olsen's Danish Village Bakery. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @following.mels, @antoniogtzv,@lisaleephotography, @fullbellyely⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #SolvangUSA

node.text:
Join us for a game called 'Spot the bridge' in @VisitSanDiego. ⁣
⁣
It's a super easy game once you realize there's a 5.5-mile city hike dedicated to just that! The 7 Bridges Hike starts at the Park Boulevard Bridge, near the rose garden in #BalboaPark, and includes a suspension bridge across Kate Sessions Canyon, a wooden trestle bridge from 1905, and the city’s only steel arch bridge.⁣
⁣
This pic is of #CabrilloBridge which connects to @balboapark. Swipe to see the view from the bridge. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @mekwanders, @wizardelite⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #VisitSD

node.text:
We love our state and national parks, seashores, monuments, and preserves. And we get the impression that you folks are fans yourselves! We all have a role to play in preserving our home. Here are some things to keep in mind as you plan your travels: ⁣
⁣
🌳  Do your research: national parks are managed by the federal government, not the state. Even though national park roads, trails, and sights are open, some facilities and programs may still have restrictions and closures. ⁣
🌳  Plan ahead: Many parks require day-use reservations, including booking in your camping or lodging reservations. ⁣
🌳  Be flexible. If Plan A doesn't work out, there's likely to be plenty of beautiful alternatives down the road. ⁣
🌳  Respect your fellow traveler: be mindful of others on trails and pack out anything you take in with you. ⁣
⁣
📷. : @sammysunphoto⁣
📍 : Montaña de Oro State Park⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #RespectCalifornia

node.text:
“I never have to check the weather in the morning. I can just put on my flip-flops and shorts, then go sit in the park and read or sit on the beach and enjoy life." ⁣
⁣
Kerry Dunne came to @VisitSanDiego from Ireland for an 18-month program at @hiltonbayfront. More than eight years on, she still can’t get enough of this sunny city. Here are her top picks: ⁣
⁣
🍽️ Restaurant hopping at @littleitalysd. ⁣
🍺 Good beer and food trucks at @mikehessbrewing.
⚾ Baseball (and occasional fireworks!) at @petcopark. ⁣
⁣
Head to our link in bio for more of Kerry’s ideas on having a perfect #SanDiego day. ⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia

node.text:
Oh, hey guys 👋🏼 🐳 🐳⁣
⁣
With 840 miles of coastline, the odds of seeing whales are pretty high! Each year you can spy gray, humpback and blue whales on their annual migration between Alaska and Mexico (and back again). @lukes_images caught a glimpse of these two humpbacks at @SeeMonterey. ⁣
⁣
Where have you gone #whalewatching in California?⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #SeeMonterey

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by visitcalifornia in Santa Barbara, California with @alisandoval1, and @visitsantabarbara. May be an image of ocean and nature.

node.text:
If you picture yourself sailing off into the sunset like the closing scene of a rom-com, here are a few options for making it happen in real life: ⁣
⁣
⛵️ Book in a lesson at the @sbsailing, which offers a variety of sail and powerboat rentals to help visitors explore the nearby @ChannelIslandsNPS. Or, better yet arrange for a captain to do the steering instead. ⁣
⛵️ Check out @princechartershb for their private cruises onboard a restored classic wooden boat or a vintage yacht in @SurfCityUSA's #HuntingtonHarbor.⁣
⛵️ Set sail in @VisitSanDiego on @svcloudia, a rare restored Norwegian double-ended ketch based on naval designs from the 19th century.⁣
⁣
📷 : @alisandoval1 ⁣
📍: @VisitSantaBarbara⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia #SeeSB

node.text:
When it comes to #LosAlamos, all we ask is that you take things slow. Sleep in, have a leisurely brunch, meander to wineries, chill by the pool. The slower pace is what the locals expect of you. ⁣
⁣
You'll find this small town at the north end of the @VisitSYV, about 2.5 hours from @DiscoverLA and an hour from @VisitSantaBarbara. ⁣
⁣
🍽 Eat: @fulloflifefoods for flatbread pizzas baked in a hearth right there in the dining room. ⁣
🍷 Drink: @lofiwine for sipping natural wines while listening to the owner's extensive record collection. ⁣
👀  See: Cruise along Bell Street for some locally-made finds. Start at @sistersgiftsandhome, and stop by @losalamosgallery and @bodegalosalamos to see local art. ⁣
🛌 Stay: at one of the six themed suites at @thevicklosalamos. ⁣
⁣
📷 : @livelikeitsthewknd, @danielmpetersen, @outboundweekend, @afarmedia ⁣
.⁣
#VisitCalifornia
